  "prompt": "What are some of the funniest movies you've ever seen?",
  "response": "There are many films that are considered classics in the realm of comedy. Here are some of the funniest movies that have made audiences laugh over the years:\n\n1. **Airplane! (1980)** - A parody of disaster films, this movie is packed with visual and verbal puns.\n\n2. **Monty Python and the Holy Grail (1975)** - A hilarious take on the legend of King Arthur, filled with absurd humor and iconic quotes.\n\n3. **Groundhog Day (1993)** - Bill Murray delivers a brilliant comedic performance in this story about a man reliving the same day over and over.\n\n4. **The Big Lebowski (1998)** - A cult classic that follows \"The Dude\" in a comedic noir mystery filled with eccentric characters.\n\n5. **Superbad (2007)** - A coming-of-age teen comedy that captures the awkwardness of high school and friendship.\n\n6. **Bridesmaids (2011)** - This film broke stereotypes in the genre with its hilarious and heartfelt depiction of female friendship.\n\n7. **Step Brothers (2008)** - A comedy about two middle-aged, lazy stepbrothers that is both absurd and laugh-out-loud funny.\n\n8. **The Hangover (2009)** - A wild night in Las Vegas leads to hilarious situations and unforgettable moments.\n\n9. **Ferris Bueller's Day Off (1986)** - A charming story about a high school student who fakes being sick to enjoy a day off, filled with witty humor.\n\n10. **Mean Girls (2004)** - A sharp and funny take on high school cliques, written by Tina Fey.\n\nEach of these films has its own unique style of humor, making them favorites among many comedy fans.",
